translated: Cederberg, Hans Wilhelm, provincial doctor, Gusum, born on March 19th, 1899 in Östra Vemmenhög, Malmöhus county, son of the vicar W.C. and Maria Cegrell. Married to Brita Svensson in 1927 and had four children: Lars (born 1928), Ake (1932), Kerstin (1935), and Anders (1941). He graduated from Lund University with a degree in medicine in 1923 and obtained a medical license in 1928. He worked as a physician in various districts including Skurup and Ljungsäter, and also served as an assistant physician at Sahlgr. Hospital and Strängnäs’ Hospital. He was a member of the medical staff at various clinics and hospitals in Lund, including the ear, nose and throat clinic, and the epidemic hospital. He was appointed as a provincial physician in Gusum in 1940, and became regular provincial doctor in 1946. He was awarded a scholarship by the Navy for medical studies in 1928-1930 and served as a Navy doctor. He was promoted to second and first lieutenant in 1930 and 1939, respectively.
